{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0b15936a-3669-4172-9108-de3a38a5cb99","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", while `=` means exact match. You can also combine filters, e.g. `--filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests&TestCategory=Unit\"`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0fda8f78-1b9c-4286-874b-b347b16918ad","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about dotnet CLI usage.","outputTokens":159,"requestId":"67C9:2FF63B:2C2082F:30B2FA3:69FD3CEF"},"id":"4f728d2b-c273-4c66-b673-43cc6e49bd5d","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:31:35.564Z","parentId":"e6e004b0-90b8-4422-b838-8db453852db0"}
